The Principal of the Government Girls Secondary School (GGSS) Abaji, Hajiya Rukaiyyat Adaviruku, has said the school’s goal is for students to acquire values and life skills that will help them live better lives in tomorrow’s world. Adaviruku stated this in her welcome address on the occasion of the graduation ceremony of 114 students of the Class of 2019 at the school on Saturday. She said it was in pursuance of the school’s goal that a modern fish pond was being constructed to boost the entrepreneurial skills of students in the sector. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE She said the school also saw the need to improve security network and  embarked on the installation of solar system and CCTV gadgets in the school. She added that the school has also constructed four blocks of additional toilets to enhance sanitation of the school. Also speaking, the chairman of the FCT Secondary Education Board (SEB) Alhaji Musa Yahaya Muhammad, represented by head of department for Curriculum, Mr. Goro Alhamdu, commended the school management for its efforts in keeping the flag flying. He congratulated the graduating students and urged them to be good ambassadors of the school wherever they went.  GGSS Abaji graduates 91 students GGSS Abaji wins JA Nigeria entrepreneur contest GGSS Abaji graduates 64 students Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin